\newlabel{fig:minority_violin}{{14}{23}{Per-sample predicted probability for the correct class on minority classes. NN (blue) assigns higher probabilities than MLU-CB (green) on Pineal/CP samples (NN median 0.20 vs MLU 0.14; 42.3\% vs 23.1\% above threshold). On Sellar, both models perform well (NN 90.6\% vs MLU 70.3\% above threshold), but NN is more confident}{figure.caption.31}{}}
