\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {15}{\ignorespaces Model diversity analysis. Left: pairwise prediction disagreement rate. The 3 MLU models show low mutual disagreement ($\sim $2--5\%) since they share the same features. NN and ImgTab disagree most with MLU models ($\sim $15--28\%). Right: error pattern correlation. MLU models make the same mistakes (high correlation $\sim $0.83--0.94), while NN makes different errors (low correlation $\sim $0.34--0.48 with other models), explaining its ensemble contribution.}}{24}{figure.caption.32}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ensemble_diversity}{{15}{24}{Model diversity analysis. Left: pairwise prediction disagreement rate. The 3 MLU models show low mutual disagreement ($\sim $2--5\%) since they share the same features. NN and ImgTab disagree most with MLU models ($\sim $15--28\%). Right: error pattern correlation. MLU models make the same mistakes (high correlation $\sim $0.83--0.94), while NN makes different errors (low correlation $\sim $0.34--0.48 with other models), explaining its ensemble contribution}{figure.caption.32}{}}
